# Trading System Rules

## Configuration Management
- **Define configuration values and symbol lists centrally** in `src/utils/trading_config.py`
- **Avoid duplicating configuration** across multiple files
- **Use environment variables** for environment-specific settings
- **Implement configuration validation** to catch errors early
- **Document all configuration options** with clear descriptions

## AI Integration
- **Include news events in LLM-based sentiment analysis** for trading strategies
- **Use Ollama for local LLM processing** to reduce latency and costs
- **Implement proper error handling** for AI service calls with fallbacks
- **Cache AI responses** when appropriate to improve performance
- **Monitor AI service performance** and costs

## Trading Strategy Development
- **Implement strategies in the `src/strategies/` directory** following established patterns
- **Use the established strategy base classes** for consistency
- **Include proper risk management** in all strategies (position sizing, stop-losses)
- **Test strategies thoroughly** before deployment with backtesting
- **Document strategy logic and parameters** clearly

## Backtesting Framework
- **Use the established backtesting framework** for consistency
- **Implement proper performance metrics** (Sharpe ratio, drawdown, etc.)
- **Include transaction costs** in backtesting for realistic results
- **Test strategies across different market conditions** (bull, bear, sideways)
- **Document backtesting results and assumptions** for reproducibility

## Risk Management
- **Implement position sizing rules** based on volatility and account size
- **Use stop-loss and take-profit mechanisms** to manage risk
- **Monitor portfolio risk metrics** (VaR, correlation, concentration)
- **Implement proper risk alerts** for unusual market conditions
- **Document risk management procedures** and limits

## Data Management
- **Use the established market data services** for consistency
- **Implement proper data caching strategies** to reduce API costs
- **Use the options data service** for options-related operations
- **Implement data validation and quality checks** at ingestion
- **Monitor data freshness and availability** for trading decisions

## Performance Monitoring
- **Use structured logging** throughout the trading application
- **Monitor trading performance metrics** in real-time
- **Implement proper error tracking** for strategy failures
- **Use the established monitoring infrastructure** (Prometheus, Grafana)
- **Document monitoring procedures** and alert thresholds

## API Design
- **Follow RESTful API design principles** for trading APIs
- **Use proper HTTP status codes** for error handling
- **Implement API versioning** for backward compatibility
- **Include proper API documentation** with examples
- **Use authentication and authorization** for all trading endpoints

## Testing
- **Write comprehensive tests** for all trading logic
- **Use mock data for testing** to avoid market data costs
- **Test edge cases and error conditions** thoroughly
- **Implement integration tests** for critical trading paths
- **Maintain high test coverage** for trading strategies

## Deployment
- **Deploy strategies through Kubernetes** for scalability and reliability
- **Use rolling updates** to avoid trading interruptions
- **Implement proper health checks** for trading services
- **Monitor strategy performance** in production
- **Have rollback procedures** for failed strategy deployments
